GEOG 656 FINAL PROJECT

Red Fox Population in Prince George's County

Final Project in Jupyter Notebook

Data Collected is as Follow:

  • iNaturalist Red Fox Population of 2020 in Prince George County: https://www.inaturalist.org/observations?place_id=any&subview=map
  • Maryland 2017 Road Centerlines Per County: https://data.imap.maryland.gov/datasets/maryland::maryland-road-centerlines-comprehensive/about
  • Maryland 2020 Census and County: https://planning.maryland.gov/MSDC/Pages/census/Census2020/pL_2020redistricting.aspx
  • Major Maryland Cities 2017: https://hub.arcgis.com/datasets/17b5029d658644d4b5e534f73b162065/explore?location=38.957844%2C-76.797811%2C10.09

Map the iNaturalist Points within PGCo

In [22]:
# Create a GeoDatarame
    # https://geopandas.org/en/stable/docs/reference/geodataframe.html
gdf_pg_county = gpd.GeoDataFrame(iNaturalist_PG_2020, geometry=geometry)

# Ensure the CRS matches PG_merged_gdf
gdf_pg_county.crs = PG_merged_gdf.crs

# Spatial join: make sure points are WITHIN PG County boundary
gdf_pg_county = gdf_pg_county[gdf_pg_county.geometry.within(PG_merged_gdf.unary_union)]

# Plotting the data: Base Layer is Prince George's County
base = PG_merged_gdf.plot(edgecolor='black')  # Plot PG County boundary
gdf_pg_county.plot(ax=base, color='red', markersize=25, edgecolor='black')  # Plot points within PG County
plt.title("iNaturalist Observations within Prince George's County, Maryland")
plt.xlabel('Longitude')
plt.ylabel('Latitude')

# Show the county without any text above
plt.show()

In [25]:
# Make sure ALL GeoDataFrames have the same CRS
PG_County_Roads = PG_County_Roads.to_crs(PG_merged_gdf.crs)
gdf_pg_county.crs = PG_merged_gdf.crs
cities_gdf = MD_major_cities.to_crs(PG_merged_gdf.crs)

# Filter the cities to only include those within Prince George's County
    # How to process the within: https://geopandas.org/en/stable/docs/reference/api/geopandas.GeoSeries.within.html
    # How to select the area for the counties with the area for the https://geopandas.org/en/v0.10.0/docs/reference/api/geopandas.GeoSeries.unary_union.html
PGCo_cities = cities_gdf[cities_gdf.geometry.within(PG_merged_gdf.unary_union)]

# Plotting the data: Ensuring the map is large enough to hold the legend
    # DONT INCLUDE base as "PG_merged_gdf"
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))

# Plot the population distribution in Prince George's County
    # Twilight is a cool color!!!! https://matplotlib.org/stable/users/explain/colors/colormaps.html
PG_merged_gdf.plot(ax=ax, column='Total Population:', legend=True, edgecolor='black', cmap='twilight')

# Plot the roads within Prince George's County
PG_County_Roads.plot(ax=ax, color='black', linewidth=0.25, label='Roads')

# Plot the iNaturalist points within Prince George's County on top of the roads
gdf_pg_county.plot(ax=ax, color='red', markersize=25, zorder=5, label='iNaturalist Observations', edgecolor='black')  # Increased markersize and zorder for top layering

# Plot the cities within Prince George's County on top of everything else
PGCo_cities.plot(ax=ax, color='blue', markersize=25, zorder=4, label='Cities', edgecolor='black')

# Set the title and labels
plt.title("Prince George's County, Cities, iNaturalist Observations, Roads, and Population Total (2020 Census Data)")
plt.xlabel('Longitude')
plt.ylabel('Latitude')

# Show legend 
ax.legend()

# Show the county without any text above
plt.show()

Create a Buffer: Display the iNaturalist Observations and the Major Cities within PGCo

  • 1.5km buffer of the various major cities to the iNaturalist Red Fox Popuation
  • This is equivalent to about 1mi distance
In [27]:
buffer_distance = 0.015  # CRS is in degrees: 0.015 degrees ABOUT 1.5 km

# Create a buffer around each city in PGCo_cities
    # How to do buffers :) https://geopandas.org/en/stable/docs/reference/api/geopandas.GeoSeries.buffer.html
PGCo_city_buffers = PGCo_cities.copy()
PGCo_city_buffers['geometry'] = PGCo_city_buffers.buffer(buffer_distance)

# Filter iNaturalist observations within the city buffers
pg_inaturalist_within_buffer = gdf_pg_county[gdf_pg_county.geometry.within(PGCo_city_buffers.unary_union)]

# Plotting the data
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))

# Use for colors!!!! https://matplotlib.org/stable/users/explain/colors/colormaps.html
# Plot the population distribution in Prince George's County
PG_merged_gdf.plot(ax=ax, column='Total Population:', legend=True, edgecolor='black', cmap='twilight')

# Plot the roads within Prince George's County
PG_County_Roads.plot(ax=ax, color='darkgrey', linewidth=0.25, label='Roads')

# Plot the buffers around the cities with enhanced clarity
    # Gained from ChatGPT to access
PGCo_city_buffers.plot(
    ax=ax, 
    color='yellow', 
    alpha=0.4,  # Slightly transparent
    edgecolor='brown',  # Dark blue edge color
    linewidth=2,  # Slightly thicker edges
    linestyle='--',  # Dashed line style for the edges
)

# Plot the iNaturalist points within the city buffers
pg_inaturalist_within_buffer.plot(ax=ax, color='red', markersize=25, zorder=5, label='iNaturalist Observations within Buffer', edgecolor='black')

# Plot the cities within Prince George's County on top of everything else
PGCo_cities.plot(ax=ax, color='blue', markersize=50, zorder=4, label='Cities', edgecolor='black')

# Set the title and labels
plt.title("Prince George's County: iNaturalist Observations within a 1.5km Buffer Around Major Cities")
plt.xlabel('Longitude')
plt.ylabel('Latitude')

# Show legend
ax.legend()

# Show the plot
plt.show()
